According to [this link](https://www.testcontainers.org/features/networking/), `withExposedPorts()` --&gt; this exposed port number is from the perspective of the container. &lt;br/&gt;
From the host&#39;s perspective Testcontainers actually exposes this on a random free port. This is by design, to avoid port collisions that may arise with locally running software or in between parallel test runs. &lt;br/&gt;
Because there is this layer of indirection, it is necessary to ask Testcontainers for the actual mapped port at runtime. This can be done using the `getMappedPort` method, which takes the original (container) port as an argument: &lt;br/&gt;

    Integer firstMappedPort = container.getMappedPort(yourExposedPort);&lt;br/&gt;
Try to connect with DBeaver to the port that appears first.

